00:55:30.400 --> 00:55:31.400
of weird math that goes into designing Choose
Your Own Adventure, like the flow-charting.

00:55:31.400 --> 00:55:32.400
'Cause I stupidly, 'cause I knew this math,
I completely screwed it up.

00:55:32.400 --> 00:55:33.400
I started--.

00:55:33.400 --> 00:55:34.400
The way I'd been doing it, is I flow chart
in the abstract what a story should be like

00:55:34.400 --> 00:55:35.400
and then I assign stuff to the scenes.

00:55:35.400 --> 00:55:36.400
And if you wanna have a bridge, a fork, at
every point, you want to have a choice at

00:55:36.400 --> 00:55:37.400
every point, you have to--.

00:55:37.400 --> 00:55:38.400
It's two to the N plus one plus two to the
N plus one.

00:55:38.400 --> 00:55:39.400
So, by the time you've gotten to two to the
tenth, which is to say you've only read ten

00:55:39.400 --> 00:55:40.400
scenes, you have something like 15 hundred
scenes you have to write to make the reader

00:55:40.400 --> 00:55:41.400
able to do that, right?

00:55:41.400 --> 00:55:42.400
So, you have to figure out a reasonable, but
still fun, way to clip.

00:55:42.400 --> 00:55:43.400
So, the cool thing is if you clip at a branch,
you clip off two to the N from that point,

00:55:43.400 --> 00:55:44.400
right?

00:55:44.400 --> 00:55:45.400
Two to the N plus two to the N plus one and
so on.

00:55:45.400 --> 00:55:46.400
And so, it's not as scary if you just learn
how to clip judiciously.

00:55:46.400 --> 00:55:47.400
But so, there is, it's an interesting thing
and you can even look at flow charts and you

00:55:47.400 --> 00:55:48.400
can tell the genre.

00:55:48.400 --> 00:55:49.400
I don't mean a genre like whether it's a Western
or not, but there's a genre of whether it's

00:55:49.400 --> 00:55:50.400
a what type of story they're telling from
just looking at the flow chart.

00:55:50.400 --> 00:55:51.400
So like, the old Choose Your Own Adventure
that you read when you were 12, the little

00:55:51.400 --> 00:55:52.400
simple one that actually says "Choose Your
Own Adventure" on the top, the flowchart,

00:55:52.400 --> 00:55:53.400
you could make it fan out in every direction
'cause there are lots of short stories with

00:55:53.400 --> 00:55:54.400
choices.

00:55:54.400 --> 00:55:55.400
In fact, it might even be two to the N plus
two to the N plus one and so on, because you

00:55:55.400 --> 00:55:56.400
really basically have a simple fork at each
point.

00:55:56.400 --> 00:55:57.400
And to get to the end might only be ten steps.

00:55:57.400 --> 00:55:58.400
And the way you play this is you try to do
all the different routes, right?

00:55:58.400 --> 00:55:59.400
Whereas, if--.

00:55:59.400 --> 00:56:00.400
So, if you look at the flow chart, it would
either look like that or it would look like

00:56:00.400 --> 00:56:01.400
