It's like D and D for one.

00:56:06.400 --> 00:56:07.400
[laughter]

00:56:07.400 --> 00:56:08.400
I've seen a couple of these games.

00:56:08.400 --> 00:56:09.400
There's a very popular one--

00:56:09.400 --> 00:56:10.400
&gt;&gt;MALE #33: If you pick up the sword three
steps ago, then--

00:56:10.400 --> 00:56:11.400
&gt;&gt;Zach Weinersmith: It's exactly like that,
yeah.

00:56:11.400 --> 00:56:12.400
And what's interesting though is to make that
work, you have to have a much more linear

00:56:12.400 --> 00:56:13.400
flow because you're telling one story, right?

00:56:13.400 --> 00:56:14.400
And also, if it's stuff like you have to have
the sword to kill the whatever, you have to

00:56:14.400 --> 00:56:15.400
